n, dream of a president lying dead in the White House? All of these questions, and many others, arise from recollective "ations of Lincoln, and the answer in each instance depends upon how one appraises the reliability of such recollection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aHistory -- United States. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh1 aFehrenbacher, Don E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFehrenbacher, Virginia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476488940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804764889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804764889/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles